Steps to reproduce
# Create a review with "Search for Files" option e.g go to {{Create review > Add content > Search For Files"}}
# It happens when you have multiple revisions to the same file
# Try to search using the advance query:
{noformat}
select revisions from dir / where (in or before any open,closed review) and comment matches "MP-1" 
order by date desc group by changeset return path, revision, author, date, csid
{noformat}
# See the [screen shot|^add.png], the "Add all 4 revisions" doesn't work as expected

{quote}
getting the site url is a good fallback, but a more foolproof approach is to snif the address bar (Window.Location) in the browser with JS and post it to this action, for use generating this url (or something). 

That is, no amount of server-side guessing (which may be 95% accurate) will be as good as the value of the location bar, which is canonically the url we want punters to come back to.
{quote}
